---
By: Henry T. Hamblin
Locus:
  Page: 503
  Verse: 8
Tags:
  - Worry
---
It is the ambition of many to live without working. What they desire is a
parasitic life, in which they take everything, but give nothing in return.
This is against the principle of Life, and those who try to act in this
manner bring a blight upon themselves.
